## Authorization

### Admin Role Checks

Every admin API route enforces role checks:

```typescript
// Middleware
export function requireAdminLevel(minLevel: number) {
  return async (req: Request, res: Response, next: NextFunction) => {
    const session = await getServerSession();
    if (!session) {
      return res.status(401).json({ error: "Unauthorized" });
    }

    const roleLevel = getRoleLevel(session.adminRole);
    if (roleLevel > minLevel) {
      return res.status(403).json({ error: "Forbidden: insufficient role" });
    }

    req.admin = { id: session.user.id, role: session.adminRole };
    next();
  };
}
```

### Resource Ownership

Players can only access their own resources:

```typescript
// Bot command
const discordUserId = interaction.user.id;
const character = await api.getCharacterByDiscordId(discordUserId);
if (!character) {
  return interaction.editReply({ content: "Ngươi chưa có nhân vật." });
}
```

Button/select validation:

```typescript
// Every interaction handler
const character = await getCharacterByUserId(interaction.user.id);
if (character.id !== targetId) {
  return interaction.reply({
    content: "Đây không phải nhân vật của ngươi.",
    flags: MessageFlags.Ephemeral,
  });
}
```

