## Input Validation

### Zod Schema Validation

Every API input uses Zod:

```typescript
import { z } from "zod";

const CultivateSchema = z.object({
  characterId: z.string().cuid(),
  mode: z.enum(["STABLE", "FORCED", "SECLUSION", "SECT"]),
});

export async function POST(req: Request) {
  const body = await req.json();
  const result = CultivateSchema.safeParse(body);

  if (!result.success) {
    return Response.json(
      { error: "Invalid input", details: result.error.flatten() },
      { status: 400 }
    );
  }

  // Proceed with validated input
  const { characterId, mode } = result.data;
  // ...
}
```

### Discord Input Validation

- Slash command options have type and constraints
- Button payloads are validated with Zod
- `custom_id` is parsed with explicit schema

### Character Name Validation

```typescript
const nameSchema = z
  .string()
  .min(2, "Tên phải có ít nhất 2 ký tự")
  .max(4, "Tên không quá 4 ký tự")
  .regex(/^[\p{L}\s]+$/u, "Tên chỉ được chứa chữ cái")
  .transform((v) => v.trim());
```

