## Rate Limiting

### Discord Rate Limits

Discord has built-in rate limits. Respect them:
- 1 slash command acknowledgement per 3 seconds per channel
- 200 unique button interactions per day per channel

### API Rate Limits

| Endpoint | Limit | Window |
|----------|-------|--------|
| `/api/cultivate` | 10 | per minute |
| `/api/breakthrough` | 5 | per hour |
| `/api/encounter` | 10 | per hour |
| Admin endpoints | 10 | per minute |

```typescript
// Simple in-memory rate limiter
const rateLimiter = new Map<string, { count: number; resetAt: number }>();

export function checkRateLimit(key: string, limit: number, windowMs: number): boolean {
  const now = Date.now();
  const record = rateLimiter.get(key);

  if (!record || now > record.resetAt) {
    rateLimiter.set(key, { count: 1, resetAt: now + windowMs });
    return true;
  }

  if (record.count >= limit) {
    return false;
  }

  record.count++;
  return true;
}
```

### Worker Rate Limits

BullMQ has built-in rate limiting per worker:

```typescript
const worker = new Worker("seclusion-complete", handler, {
  limiter: {
    max: 10,     // Max 10 jobs
    duration: 1000, // Per 1 second
  },
});
```

